        Creates a new method registry with a new compilable entry representing the arguments of this method call. The new entry will be matched last, i.e. other registered entries will attempted to be matched after the new entry.

        instrumentation - The instrumentation that is responsible for implementing this method.

      • compile

        public MethodRegistry.Compiled compile(InstrumentedType instrumentedType,
                                       TypeWriter.MethodPool.Entry fallback)
        Description copied from interface: MethodRegistry
        Once all entries for a method registry were registered, a method registry can be compiled in order to allow the retrieval of a compiled entry for a known method. Additionally, a fallback entry is to be supplied which is returned if a requested method is not known to the compiled method registry.
        Specified by:
        compile in interface MethodRegistry
        Parameters:
        instrumentedType - The instrumented type for which this field registry is to be compiled.
        fallback - The fallback field attribute appender factory that serves as a fallback for unknown methods.
        Returns:
        A compiled method registry representing the methods that were registered with this method registry.
